name: Riders of Rohan (The Lord of the Rings Commander Precon Decklist)

main.name: Éowyn, Shieldmaiden
main.oracle_text:
First strike
At the beginning of combat on your turn, if another Human entered the battlefield under your control this turn, create two 2/2 red Human Knight creature tokens with trample and haste. Then if you control six or more Humans, draw a card.

card.name: Sol Ring
card.oracle_text: {T}: Add {C}{C}.
card.flavor_text: In the Second Age, Sauron was not yet evil to behold, and the Elven-smiths of Eregion received his aid and grew mighty in craft, whereas he learned all their secrets, and betrayed them, and forged secretly in the Mountain of Fire the One Ring to be their master.

card.set_name: The Lord of the Rings: Tales of Middle-earth
card.name: Prince Imrahil the Fair
card.oracle_text: Whenever you draw your second card each turn, create a 1/1 white Human Soldier creature token.
card.flavor_text: "The Lord Aragorn I hold to be my liege lord, whether he claim it or no. His wish is to me a command."

card.name: Field of Ruin
card.oracle_text:
{T}: Add {C}.
{2}, {T}, Sacrifice Field of Ruin: Destroy target nonbasic land an opponent controls. Each player searches their library for a basic land card, puts it onto the battlefield, then shuffles.
card.flavor_text:
"There's some devilry at work in the Shire."
—Sam

card.name: Evolving Wilds
card.oracle_text: {T}, Sacrifice Evolving Wilds: Search your library for a basic land card, put it onto the battlefield tapped, then shuffle.
card.flavor_text:
When winter first begins to bite
and stones crack in the frosty night,
when pools are black and trees are bare,
'tis evil in the Wild to fare.

card.name: Banishing Light
card.oracle_text: When Banishing Light enters, exile target nonland permanent an opponent controls until Banishing Light leaves the battlefield.
card.flavor_text: Before all went Aragorn with the Flame of the West—Andúril, like a new fire kindled, Narsil reforged as deadly as of old. And upon his brow was the Star of Elendil.

card.set_name: The Lord of the Rings: Tales of Middle-earth
card.name: Théoden, King of Rohan
card.oracle_text: Whenever Théoden, King of Rohan or another Human you control enters, target creature gains double strike until end of turn.
card.flavor_text: "Dark have been my dreams of late, but I feel new-awakened. I only fear that already you have come too late, Gandalf."

card.set_name: The Lord of the Rings: Tales of Middle-earth
card.name: Lost to Legend
card.oracle_text: Put target nonland historic permanent into its owner's library fourth from the top. (Artifacts, legendaries, and Sagas are historic.)
card.flavor_text:
"In the days of Isildur, the Ruling Ring passed out of all knowledge."
—Elrond

card.set_name: The Lord of the Rings: Tales of Middle-earth
card.name: Erkenbrand, Lord of Westfold
card.oracle_text: Whenever Erkenbrand, Lord of Westfold or another Human you control enters, creatures you control get +1/+0 until end of turn.
card.flavor_text: Down from the hills leaped Erkenbrand, lord of Westfold, and the hosts of Isengard roared in fear.

card.name: Grey Host Reinforcements
card.oracle_text:
Flying, ward {3}
When Grey Host Reinforcements enters, exile target player's graveyard. Put a number of +1/+1 counters on Grey Host Reinforcements equal to the number of creature cards exiled this way.
card.flavor_text:
"I hope they haven't forgotten how to fight."
—Gimli

card.name: Beregond of the Guard
card.oracle_text: Whenever Beregond of the Guard or another Human you control enters, creatures you control get +1/+1 and gain vigilance until end of turn.
card.flavor_text:
"Beregond, if you can, do something to stop any dreadful thing from happening."
—Pippin

card.name: Champions of Minas Tirith
card.oracle_text:
When Champions of Minas Tirith enters, you become the monarch.
At the beginning of combat on each opponent's turn, if you're the monarch, that opponent may pay {X}, where X is the number of cards in their hand. If they don't, they can't attack you this combat.
card.flavor_text: "The Realm of Sauron is ended forever!"

card.name: Boromir, Gondor's Hope
card.oracle_text: Whenever Boromir, Gondor's Hope enters or attacks, look at the top six cards of your library. You may reveal a Human or artifact card from among them and put it into your hand. Put the rest on the bottom of your library in a random order.
card.flavor_text: "Long have I wandered by roads forgotten, seeking the house of Elrond."

card.name: Gimli of the Glittering Caves
card.oracle_text:
Double strike
Whenever another legendary creature you control enters, put a +1/+1 counter on Gimli of the Glittering Caves.
Whenever Gimli deals combat damage to a player, create a Treasure token.
card.flavor_text: "No Dwarf could be unmoved by such loveliness."

card.name: Éomer, King of Rohan
card.oracle_text:
Double strike
Éomer, King of Rohan enters with a +1/+1 counter on it for each other Human you control.
When Éomer enters, target player becomes the monarch. Éomer deals damage equal to its power to any target.

card.name: Lossarnach Captain
card.oracle_text:
First strike
Whenever Lossarnach Captain or another Human you control enters, tap target creature an opponent controls.
At the beginning of your upkeep, create a 1/1 white Human Soldier creature token.

card.oracle_text:
When your commander deals combat damage to a player, if there is no monarch, you become the monarch.
At the beginning of the monarch's end step, that player draws a card.
card.flavor_text: "If indeed you look only, as you say, for records of ancient days and the beginnings of the City, read on!"

card.oracle_text:
Enchant creature

card.flavor_text:
"We must hasten. The beacons of Gondor are alight. War is kindled."
—Gandalf

card.name: Faramir, Steward of Gondor
card.oracle_text:
Whenever a legendary creature you control with mana value 4 or greater enters, you become the monarch.
At the beginning of your end step, if you're the monarch, create two 1/1 white Human Soldier creature tokens.
card.flavor_text: "The last Steward of Gondor begs leave to surrender his office."

If you don't, at the beginning of the next end step, return that card to the battlefield under its owner's control with a vigilance counter and a lifelink counter on it.
card.flavor_text: "Ónen i-Estel Edain, ú-chebin estel anim."

card.flavor_text: "You may triumph on the field, for a day. But against the Power that now arises there is no victory."

card.oracle_text:
Create X 2/2 red Human Knight creature tokens with trample and haste.
Whenever one or more creatures you control deal combat damage to one or more players this turn, you become the monarch.
card.flavor_text: "A sword-day, a red day, ere the sun rises! Ride now, ride now! Ride to Gondor!"

I — Create two 1/1 white Human Soldier creature tokens.

—Aragorn

—Théoden

card.oracle_text:
You have no maximum hand size.

card.flavor_text: The high throne was empty. At the foot of its dais, upon the lowest step which was broad and deep, there was a stone chair, black and unadorned, for the Steward of Gondor.

Not all those who wander are lost;
The old that is strong does not wither,
